    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1916-01-19T11:41:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1916-01-19T11:41:00-05:00" n="713"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d713">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 165.102/807</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in the Netherlands</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_LM1"
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Langhorne</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">The Hague</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1916-01-19T17:00:00+00:19">
                            <hi rend="italic">January 19, 1916, 5 p. m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received 12 p. m.</hi>]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>487. For Department of Commerce.</p>
                <list>
                    <item>87. Await your answer my 86. Have reliable information to the effect that
                        might obtain 800 tons colors if I can go to Berlin next Monday with a <pb
                            facs="0837" n="551" xml:id="pg_551"/> guarantee that British Navy will
                        not interfere. Important that you should answer at once. What are the
                        prospects? <persName corresp="#p_TEW1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Thompson</hi>
                        </persName>, <hi rend="italic">Commercial Attaché</hi>
                    </item>
                </list>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_LM1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Langhorne</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
